<br>
I also tried to take on the bloodgill maurader, just to liven things up.  I dove down to the temple entrance, and pulled one of the bloodgills outside the entrance.  That brought the bloodgill from the other side of the entrance and the maurader.  I alternated both pet heals and SoS when it was safe.  It was close, but good ole' Jabober and I were able to pull it out.  The good thing about that is the maurader apparently has a long spawn time, so the next 4-5 times I visited the entrance, I never saw him.  This frees up the gobs around the entrance to be easy pickings.<br>
<br>
After a 1 yellow bubble detour in OOT, visiting Gornit and the seafuries, I came back to the bloodgills to see how they were at 49.  With the new 49 firepet and KEI, I was able to get 2 yellow bubbles in 90 minutes.  If you thought that Jabober at 44 tore through the gobbies, you should see him at 49!  Instead of using SoS for the killshot, I used Blaze to 'tag' the gobbies and let the pet finish them off.  It's much more mana friendly, and reduces the chance of accidental aggro.<br>
<br>
Anyway, sorry for my ramblings, I just had to rave about this spot.  I highly recommend anyone to go here, if only to break up the monotony of the DL grind.<br>
<br>
